   For me it is the note Bridget scribbled to Mike when they were
reunited in the hospital, where at first a respirator prevented her
from talking:

   Relying on the company's data, the FDA accepted Warner-Lambert's
recommendation to place language on the label reflecting 48 cases;
the new label would call the incidence of liver failure "very rare."

